public conversations, political debate, urban policy and planning, and scholarly discovery, it is both a fascinating case study and an accessible introduction to the theory and practice of urban sustainability. A clear-eyed view of the struggles of turning knowledge into action, this book illuminates the places where theory and reality converge and presents an approach to municipal development, planning, and governance that takes seriously the urgent need to address climate change and injustice.Addressing a wide variety of topics and themes, including energy, diversity, economic development, and ecological health, Sustainability Matters is both a critique of current practice and a vision for the future that uses the city of Calgary as a microcosm to address issues faced by cities around the world. This is essential reading not only for every Calgarian working for a vibrant and sustainable future, but for all those interested in in the future of cities in a post-carbon world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCity planningxEnvironmental aspectszAlbertazCalgary. 0aCity planningxEnvironmental aspects. 0aSustainable livingzAlbertazCalgary. 0aSustainable urban developmentzAlbertazCalgary. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Development / Sustainable Development.2bisacsh  acarbon zero.  aenergy transitions.  aenvrionmental studies.  aequity.  afossil fuel transition.  afossil fuel.  agrowth economics.  anet zero carbon.  ano-growth economics.  arenewable energy.  asustainability.  asustainable cities.  asustainable development.  asustainable energy.  aurban design.  aurban governance.  aurban planning.  aurban studies.1 aGhitter, Geoff, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKeough, Noel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08i